{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"093d2178-8286-4ca0-9606-ca2d3786818b","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier; it's no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYour project already has `EnableMSTestRunner` set, which is correct. I'll clean up the obsolete property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013ZNhDL9vvngwCCVWKkuJUT","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-39ab0c770d5447deb7fb9ed0daf7a204/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-39ab0c770d5447deb7fb9ed0daf7a204/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"6748ac85-466c-4aca-9ae0-e6dfbef84b92","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to bridge `dotnet test` (which used VSTest) with MTP-based test projects.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP natively, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\n\nNow I'll show them how to update their project file to remove that property.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"0431:D1352:1DF4310:21C99EB:69E81AC2"},"id":"3ba11827-163c-4abe-9a1a-3068516dda4f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:10.295Z","parentId":"7f1e0830-cf6e-40d3-be8c-3aae5187924e"}
