{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af81ce87-be2f-478e-9f07-0d22a78eaf8a","content":"**Summary:**\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` — removed.** It was only needed in .NET 9 to make `dotnet test` (which used VSTest under the hood) talk to MTP-based runners. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` speaks MTP natively.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner` — keep it.** This tells MSTest to build your project as an MTP executable, which is still required.\n- **`OutputType: Exe` — keep it.** MTP runners need the project to produce an executable.\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP directly with no compatibility shim.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6748ac85-466c-4aca-9ae0-e6dfbef84b92","outputTokens":160,"requestId":"0431:D1352:1DF5D8B:21CB96C:69E81ACB"},"id":"b82e5771-d8c8-4be9-b209-d4a0a818a6d9","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:16.622Z","parentId":"0f20eb84-9248-4b80-9a58-ba6c154047e1"}
